HashMappedAdvice - Class in lu.uni.geko.weaver
An implementation of the convenience representation (or proxy) of an Advice that uses a HashMap to map advice content elements to their advice instantiation scope.

Attention: The collections returned by this implementation are backed up.

haveEqualReference(EObject, EObject, EReference) - Method in class lu.uni.geko.util.ecore.UnorderedReferencesRespectingEqualityHelper
A re-implementation of EqualityHelper.haveEqualReference(EObject, EObject, EReference) that considers values of unordered references as equal if they contain the same elements in different order.

An explanation for the fact that the implementation of EcoreUtil.EqualityHelper behaves differently can be found at bugs.eclipse.org/bugs/show_bug.cgi?id=369661).

Attention: This implementation should be optimised for performance before it is used for comparison of models that contain huge lists as the algorithm runs in asymptotic quadratic time!
